      <memberdef kind="function" id="xuartlite__polled__example_8c_1aafae45d01390b1f13b15fbcdaac8a448" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int UartLitePolledExample</definition>
        <argsstring>(UINTPTR BaseAddress)</argsstring>
        <name>UartLitePolledExample</name>
        <param>
          <type>UINTPTR</type>
          <declname>BaseAddress</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function does a minimal test on the UartLite device and driver as a design example. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The purpose of this function is to illustrate how to use the <ref refid="struct_x_uart_lite" kindref="compound">XUartLite</ref> component.</para><para>This function sends data and expects to receive the data through the UartLite such that a physical loopback must be done with the transmit and receive signals of the UartLite.</para><para>This function polls the UartLite and does not require the use of interrupts.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>contains the base address of the device</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>XST_SUCCESS if successful, XST_FAILURE if unsuccessful.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>- In XSCT/classic flow, DeviceId is used to look up the device configuration.<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>This function calls the UartLite driver functions in a blocking mode such that if the transmit data does not loopback to the receive, this function may not return. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
